modules.description: This module extracts version information from a Git repository, providing the current version as a string using `git describe`. It supports saving the version directly into an OCaml source file as a constant. It works with Git repositories and OCaml source files, handling version strings that may include dirty flags or custom identifiers. Use cases include embedding build versions into binaries or tracking development versions in source-controlled projects.

This module extracts version information from Git repositories and embeds it into OCaml source files as a constant. It supports version strings with dirty flags or custom identifiers, enabling precise version tracking directly from source control. Developers can use it to automatically update version constants during builds or include version metadata in binaries. Example usage includes generating a `version.ml` file containing the current Git tag or marking development versions as dirty.
